properties.occurrenceRemarks: While investigating snow leopard kill sites, we (@otocolobus) encountered two ~5 week old cubs at a secondary den site. Cubs were well hidden in a rock hollow beneath an overhanging Lonicera shrub. Wonderful to stumble upon concrete signs of successful reproduction springing from Kyrgyzstan's continued commitment to meaningful snow leopard conservation.

I am Kamal Thapa, Research Officer “mountains” at WWF Nepal. In fact I have been involving for research intensively and extensively in Kangchenjungha especially for snow leopards and blue sheep since 2006. I confirm that pugmarks (droppings) left by snow leopards which photo you have posted to us. Thank you for yours’ initiation. Best, Kamal
